  "text": "LAKESHORE, Calif. (FOX26) â€” The snow is falling on Wednesday and China Peak will be reopening on Thursday. The ski resort says it got 14\" to 16\" in the base area and even more up top. China Peak says Chair 1 will be serving Upper Dynamite, Chair 2 serving Kaiser, Chair 4 serving Lower Academy, and the new Chair 6 quad will be serving Sundown Ridge and Academy with fun terrain park features, plus the beginner hill. The trails are not yet full width so you are advised to ski and ride with care. [RELATED] [First snow in Shaver Lake, businesses prepare](https://kmph.com/news/local/first-snow-in-shaver-lake-businesses-preparing-shaver-lake-mountains-first-snostroms-powder-cabins-ski-snowboard-bussiness-resturaunts-shops-bars-rentals-inches-fun-play-family) Be prepared before you head up the mountain and make sure you dress warm and carry chains. China Peak will be open for skiing and riding from 9:00 a.m. to 4:00 p.m. Thursday through Monday for the season. [Click here](https://www.skichinapeak.com/) to visit China Peak online.",
